## Note  


Turning the front cam one graduation changes the camber about \(13^{\circ}\) and the toe- in about \(2.3mm\) {0.11 in}. Turning the rear cam one graduation changes the camber about \(8^{\circ}\) and the toe- in about \(2.3mm\) {0.11in}. If the cam cannot be turned far enough to make the adjustment, begin adjustment of the toe- in again using the other cam.  


3. Tighten the nuts.  


